It’s also a good time to look inward, for solitude, introspection, and meditation. This is also a great time for self forgiveness and forgiveness of others.

Waning Moon- this is all about releasing. This is the time to let go of all that no longer serves you. Cleansing, and breaking free from toxic habits and/or relationships. Make space for what you would like to call in on the approaching new moon.

Full Moon- the moon is fully illuminated, Making our energy and power strong at this time.  Emotions are heightened so be gentle w/ yourself. This is time to dream big, and manifest. Anything is possible. It’s also the perfect time to connect to higher powers and spirit guides.

Waxing Moon- this is the time to truly put work in towards your intentions. A time of strength, hard work, dedication, and steady energy.  A good time to launch new projects, start healthy habits, and push yourself to do the challenging work required to actualize your dreams.

New Moon- the New Moon serves as a blank slate. It’s open for the new. Start fresh, set your intentions, create and renew. This is the time to get clear on what you desire and to invite new opportunity into your life.
